room-reconstruction
===================

This repository is a derivative work that bundles the inference code of LingBot-Map
together with a metric-fusion step for ARKit room scans.

Includes code from:
  LingBot-Map (https://github.com/<upstream>/lingbot-map), licensed under Apache-2.0.
  Vendored at upstream commit 7ae07810ddac6f449f856ca0f6260ab3e1dcaa84.
  Files: the `lingbot_map/` package, `demo.py`, `pyproject.toml`, `LICENSE`.

Modifications made to the original LingBot-Map work:
  - demo.py: added a `--save_npz` flag that writes per-frame extrinsics/intrinsics and
    world_points(+conf) to a .npz (then exits before the 3D viewer), so the geometry can be
    consumed offline by the fusion step.
  - Stripped material not needed for inference: example imagery, benchmarks, the paper PDF,
    render assets, and git history.

Original work added in this repository (not part of upstream LingBot-Map):
  - fuse.py: metric fusion of the lingbot point cloud with an ARKit scan manifest via a
    full-trajectory Umeyama Sim(3) alignment.

